m_q.target_metric: Most common FIGO_stage value (mode) among samples from patients aged >70
sub_questions: What is the distribution of FIGO_stage values?
How many patients are above age 70?
Are there missing values in Age or FIGO_stage columns?

scale_issues: Age is float64 but represents whole years
Some percentage columns may be represented as decimals or percentages (e.g., Estrogen_Receptor_%)

format_notes: Data provided as CSV sample but original file is Excel (.xlsx)
First column 'idx' appears to be row identifier
Mixed data types with many object columns for categorical data

constraints: Age should be positive (0-120 reasonable range)
FIGO_stage should be categorical (IA, IB, II, III, IV, etc.)
Age > 70 filter must handle missing values appropriately
derived_filters: Consider filtering Case_excluded == 'No' if excluding poor quality samples
statistical_tests: Mode calculation for FIGO_stage in age >70 subset
output_format_requirements: Report the most common FIGO_stage value
Include count and percentage of this value among age >70 patients
Consider reporting full distribution if requested
